The Distinguished Gentleman;;1992;;R;;Comedy,Crime;;5.9;;Jonathan Lynn;;Eddie Murphy,Lane Smith,Sheryl Lee Ralph,Joe Don Baker,Victoria Rowell,Grant Shaud,Kevin McCarthy,Charles S. Dutton,Victor Rivers,Chi McBride,Sonny Jim Gaines,Noble Willingham,Gary Frank,Daniel Benzali,Cynthia Harris,Susan Forristal,Autumn Winters,James Garner;;In the conniving world of politics, even a professional shyster like Thomas Jefferson Johnson (Eddie Murphy) can find himself outmatched. After using name recognition to get elected, Johnson enjoys many of the same financial perks as other politicians. However, while investigating the connection between electric companies and cancer in young children, he unexpectedly develops a conscience. Unfortunately, fellow Congressman Dick Dodge (Lane Smith) isn't about to let him rock the boat.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0104114/